04620nam a22004695i 9780226300610DE-B159720220424125308.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220424t20212003ilu    fo  d z      eng d  a9780226300610  a(DE-B1597)575537  a(OCoLC)1058442259  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ailucUS-IL 4aQ175 7aSCI0000002bisacsh04a5011 aGodfrey-Smith, Peter, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aTheory and Reality :bAn Introduction to the Philosophy of Science /cPeter Godfrey-Smith. 1aChicago : bUniversity of Chicago Press, c[2021] 4cÂ©2003  a1 online resource (288 p.) :b6 line drawings  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aScience and Its Conceptual Foundations series00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tA Note for Those Teaching with the Book -- t1. Introduction -- t2. Logic Plus Empiricism -- t3. Induction and Confirmation -- t4. Popper: Conjecture and Refutation -- t5. Kuhn and Normal Science -- t6. Kuhn and Revolutions -- t7. Lakatos, Laudan, Feyerabend, and Frameworks -- t8. The Challenge from Sociology of Science -- t9. Feminism and Science Studies -- t10. Naturalistic Philosophy in Theory and Practice -- t11. Naturalism and the Social Structure of Science -- t12. Scientific Realism -- t13. Explanation -- t14. Bayesianism and Modern Theories of Evidence -- t15. Empiricism, Naturalism, and Scientific Realism? -- tGlossary -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aHow does science work? Does it tell us what the world is "really" like? What makes it different from other ways of understanding the universe? In Theory and Reality, Peter Godfrey-Smith addresses these questions by taking the reader on a grand tour of one hundred years of debate about science. The result is a completely accessible introduction to the main themes of the philosophy of science. Intended for undergraduates and general readers with no prior background in philosophy, Theory and Reality covers logical positivism; the problems of induction and confirmation; Karl Popper's theory of science; Thomas Kuhn and "scientific revolutions"; the views of Imre Lakatos, Larry Laudan, and Paul Feyerabend; and challenges to the field from sociology of science, feminism, and science studies. The book then looks in more detail at some specific problems and theories, including scientific realism, the theory-ladeness of observation, scientific explanation, and Bayesianism. Finally, Godfrey-Smith defends a form of philosophical naturalism as the best way to solve the main problems in the field. Throughout the text he points out connections between philosophical debates and wider discussions about science in recent decades, such as the infamous "science wars." Examples and asides engage the beginning student; a glossary of terms explains key concepts; and suggestions for further reading are included at the end of each chapter. However, this is a textbook that doesn't feel like a textbook because it captures the historical drama of changes in how science has been conceived over the last one hundred years. Like no other text in this field, Theory and Reality combines a survey of recent history of the philosophy of science with current key debates in language that any beginning scholar or critical reader can follow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  atheoretical, academic, scholarly, research, intro, philosophical, scientific, scientist, real, universe, question, history, historical, facts, interdisciplinary, accessible, undergrad, undergraduate, college, university, higher education, textbook, classroom, positivism, logic, logical, sociology, feminism, empiricism, induction, deduction, naturalism, realism.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226300610423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226300610/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles